While Australia and the UK top the list, China is the 10th most obese country in the world. Obesity rates in China are projected to rise 20 percent by 2030.

It is wonderful to see such a volume of real events accounted for by simple data sets and expressed as geographical and time ordered clocks. It is very useful for helping find the connection between events that happen in different parts of the world.

But there are also cracks in the assumptions built into the ways these events are identified and expressed. Uniquely among these clocks it comes with more than 200 original illustrations, all made by Jan Diehm with large-format format, hand-held scanners.

Nowadays, the surface of the moon is overflowing with non-functional satellites and other spacecraft, left behind by long-forgotten missions. Amateur astronomy buffs say that even Venus has a not very out of the way natural satellite , small enough to give her the title of the smallest on Earth satellite with a mass of 5,793,000 tons. Earth’s smaller neighbor, the moon, now has almost 90 natural satellites.
